{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Branch staleness detection correctly identifies branches with commits not in main, older than the configured age threshold, and no open PR.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is detector logic plus git-state reader, PR-state reader, and age-threshold config working together. A pure unit test on one function would miss wiring/contract mismatches between these modules.","test_description":"Create a local repo fixture with main and feature branches plus controlled commit timestamps, wire real staleness detector with real git-state module and a test PR-state adapter, and assert only branches meeting all three conditions are classified stale-no-pr.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.3,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Session-start setup emits a stale-work warning with actionable branch context when the current branch is stale.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily bootstrap-to-detector-to-renderer wiring. The failure is in cross-module signal propagation and message composition, not OS/network behavior.","test_description":"Run session-start initialization in-process with a stale branch state fixture from the detector interface, and assert emitted warning includes branch name, age/context, and explicit action text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A local status-classifier function maps computed branch state to labels (`clean`, `stale-no-pr`) deterministically.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Single-function deterministic mapping with no I/O; real failures are pure logic/branching errors.","test_description":"Table-drive classifier inputs to expected labels, including edge states, and run repeat invocations to verify deterministic output for identical input.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"`/kaizen-wip` against live repo and PR state distinguishes \"clean\" from \"has commits but no PR (STALE)\" in rendered output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on live repo and live PR state. Mocking can hide real failures in subprocess/git/API behavior and rendering integration.","test_description":"Execute `/kaizen-wip` end-to-end against a real test repository state and real PR backend state (or sandbox account), then assert rendered output shows `clean` vs `STALE` correctly for prepared branches.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Branches with open or merged PRs are not flagged as stale-no-PR false positives.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is contract mapping between PR-state provider and classifier logic. This can be caught with multi-module tests using realistic PR-state payloads; full live API is helpful but not always minimal.","test_description":"Wire detector + classifier with PR adapter fixtures for open and merged cases (including merged metadata), and assert stale-no-pr is never emitted for those branches.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.38,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change but branch state should no longer be classified as unPRed stale work.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure boundary is git history semantics under rebase/squash operations. Mock commit graphs often miss ancestry edge cases that real git operations expose.","test_description":"In a temporary real git repo, create feature work, then exercise rebase and squash-merge flows that rewrite hashes; run detection after each step and assert branch is not classified stale-no-pr once work is represented in main/PR history.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
